<paragraph id="8BD05346FFBAF05CFB5AFD351E7EFC10" blockId="0.[1258,2137,755,1378]" pageId="0" pageNumber="336">• Small, hornless ruminants with hindquarters considerably higher than forequarters, long, rabbit-like, upright ears, long limbs, small tail, and thick, grayish or brownish hairs, standing erect on upperparts of body; male with long, slender, curved upper canines, large glandular sac on belly, and glandulartail.</paragraph>
